		<div class="text">
		<p>
		Invert syrup is ~20% water, plus equal amounts of 
		dextrose and fructose, according to the Underbelly website.
		<p>
		</p>
		The Underbelly Standard Base (all variations) calls for 15 grams of 
		invert syrup. To substitute dry ingredients for the wet syrup,
		multiply the quantity of syrup (15) by 80% (.8 x 15 = 12) and divide 
		the result in half (12 / 2 = 6).
		<p>
		</p> 
		Add that amount (6 grams each) of dextrose and fructose to the ingredients specified 
		by the recipe.
		</p>
		<p>
		The Underbelly base recipes specify 15 grams of invert syrup, 30 grams of 
		dextrose and no fructose. So, instead of the liquid syrup, add 6 grams each of 
		fructose and dextrose.
		</p> 
